title: Arnell- Punch and the Child - Yates, BBC Con O (2009) [Philidor]
description:
Punch and the Child was a 1947 ballet of Richard Arnell's, composed towards the end of his stay in the US that was prolonged due to WWII. It is in some ways a moody and acerbic piece, since Punch adores being admired by the Child, and loves having his mischief watched, but tires easily of anybody's presence--including hers. He finally ditches her, and she stands alone, bereft at its conclusion. This became a favorite of the fine conductor Thomas Beecham, who also recorded it in the early 1950s.

Transfers are made at 768 kBits/s, directly from the disc.
